#: ../../user_guide/apps/document.rst:21
msgid "Toolbars"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/apps/document.rst:23
msgid ""
"CryptPad integrates OnlyOffice documents into the same encrypted "
"collaboration system as the other applications. Additionally OnlyOffice "
"provides a wide range of functions in a tabbed toolbar. This results in a"
" double toolbar that can cause confusion:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/apps/document.rst:25
msgid ""
"The topmost **CryptPad toolbar** is used for |file-o| **File** operations"
" (including import/export, history, properties, etc) as well as |share-"
"alt| **Share** and |unlock-alt| **Access**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/apps/document.rst:26
msgid ""
"The **OnlyOffice toolbar** is used for all functionality within the "
"document itself, as well as the collaboration modes explained in the next"
" section."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/apps/document.rst:29
msgid "Undo and collaboration modes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/apps/document.rst:34
msgid ""
"OnlyOffice provides two collaborative editing modes in documents that "
"affect how changes are synced between users and whether or not the "
"**Undo** functionality is available."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/apps/document.rst:36
msgid ""
"**Fast Mode** is enabled by default. New edits by all users are "
"automatically synced with others as they are made. In this mode it is not"
" possible to undo."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/apps/document.rst:37
msgid ""
"**Strict Mode** allows each user to make changes independently. The "
"modified cells are \"locked\" for others until the author manually saves "
"their changes. New edits are only synced with other users after being "
"saved. In this mode it is possible to undo changes that have not yet been"
" saved. When a user saves their changes, others are prompted to save in "
"order to receive the latest edits."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/apps/document.rst:39
msgid ""
"When :kbd:`Ctrl + Z` is pressed for undo, the application will "
"automatically suggest switching to **Strict Mode** to enable the undo "
"functionality."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/apps/document.rst:41
msgid ""
"To switch back to **Fast mode** use the **Collaboration** tab in the "
"OnlyOffice toolbar and select **Co-editing Mode** > **Fast**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/apps/document.rst:44
msgid ""
"CryptPad remembers your choice of editing mode on each device for all "
"documents."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/apps/document.rst:49
msgid "History"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/apps/document.rst:51
msgid ""
"To access the document history, use |file-o| **File** > |history| "
"**History** in the CryptPad toolbar."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/apps/document.rst:53
msgid ""
"Due to the integration of OnlyOffice with CryptPad's encrypted real-time "
"collaboration, history in documents works differently than :ref:`in the "
"other applications <document_history>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/apps/document.rst:58
msgid "The document history toolbar"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/apps/document.rst:60
msgid ""
"History in documents only allows to jump back to the previous version, "
"and then move forward through individual edits."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/apps/document.rst:62
msgid "|fast-backward| previous version"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/apps/document.rst:63
msgid "|step-forward| step forward one edit"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/apps/document.rst:64
msgid "|fast-forward| next version"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user_guide/apps/document.rst:66
msgid ""
"The functionality to restore and share a version, as well as everything "
"relating to :ref:`snapshots`, works in the same way as in :ref:`the other"
" applications <document_history>`."
msgstr ""

